<TITLE> US Congress backs 'generous economic support' after polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 25 (bdnews24.com)  The US Congress passed a resolution on Wednesday urging generous economic support to Bangladesh upon completion of a free and fair parliamentary election in December, the Bangladesh Embassy in Washington said. The House of Representative in its resolution, "Supporting a transition to democracy through free, fair, credible, peaceful and transparent elections in Bangladesh", made the request to the US president, an embassy statement said. Members of the House expressed their strong support for the restoration of democracy in Bangladesh. Congress also urged the caretaker government to lift the state of emergency to allow a free and fair election. The resolution was moved by the influential committee on foreign affairs with co-sponsorship by as many as forty one congressmen. Congressman Joseph Crowley, co-chair of the Congressional Bangladesh Caucus, sponsored the resolution
